Sigh! I feel a very huge lump in my throat. Today is a very important day that I nearly forgot. 

A prayer for my Dad on his birthday 🍰

Firstly thank you for being my Dad dear heavenly Father. 
You have been so good to me, you have taught me how it is like to have a father on earth. You have loved me so, to the point of saving my life at a very young age. 
You spoil me so much! You take me through the fire and make me shine like pure gold. 
If it wasn't for you, I would be sure long dead by now (people don't know this, but me and you know). Your grace keeps me even when I don't deserve it. 

Thank you for healing and delivering me from abandonment, rejection, promiscuity, lack of being raised by both my parents, abuse and so much more. You have done an incredible work in me. Heal our land I pray 🇿🇦

And so Lord...

“The king's heart is in your hand oh! LORD, like the rivers of water; You turn it wherever You wish.” 
Proverbs 21:1 

Thank you for turning my dad's heart towards you. I live to see a man who will totally surrender his life to you. A man who will tell people of your saving grace before you call him back home. In Jesus name I pray,

Amen.

I have definitely found my medication/solution for all my troubles, yes I have many of them. "Prayer" talking to God has allowed me to vent out to Him, blame someone, judge others and make myself look better before Him in prayer. He has then in return taught me how to use this time with Him wisely. Instead of doing all the above like I used to, He has taught me how to rest in Him. He has taught me to forgive, to have empathy and so many other lessons.

PRAY and all my music is available on all digital stores for you to stream, buy and enjoy. Just type in "Hlengiwe Pearl" and all my music will appear.

Happy Holidays 🎄

Last week we laid to rest my sweetheart, my handsome sweet dad. My heart is very broken I won't lie, I will miss his random phone calls, prayers, and guidance. My kids will miss the only mkhulu (grandfather) they had. 

Thank you for all the love, offerings, prayers and support we received especially from my home church #gracebiblechurch siyabonga kakhulu bazalwane.

My 83yrs old beautiful grandmother in the picture with us, my daddies mommy celebrated with us in October last year.

I am comforted by remembering and knowing that I forgave my dad for his many transgressions. I pray and hope he also forgave me for many of my own sins known and unknown to me.
I now realize that my dad fathered me/us the best way he knew how to and for that I am forever grateful. Our last phone call conversation on Christmas Day was so magical, loud and beautiful. Little did I know that would be the last day I hear his beautiful sweet voice.

FATHER'S WE NEED YOU IN REBUILDING OUR NATION 🇿🇦

God, unlike other gods is not interested in giving us what we order Him around to do for us but He is very much interested in saving our souls, changing us, working in us and giving us all we ask of Him according to His will for our own good and those coming after us. This process may feel like He is taking forever to answer our prayers, to give us what we think desperately need. We may feel like He is deaf to our prayers or that he may be failing us. But, just like any loving father he longs for us to be more like Him as He attends to our needs and wants.

- Hlengiwe Pearl

A generation that has been called to do what is right, we have been called to dust ourselves off everything that seeks to destroy us and make our lives meaningless.

Mayibuye iAfrica 🌍

This was the first time I had so much passion to want to celebrate my birthday. All thanks to a very wise old woman who taught me the importance of celebrating life daily. 

We are winning 🥂

So, yesterday there was a talk happening on the radio about women abuse. The radio host( a guy) pleaded with other men to stop abusing women, emotionally, mentally, physically, financially and...

I am also here to pass on the message to men to stop abusing women.  It's high time we all seek counseling, therapy and prayers for our inner demons. We can be freed from them, I believe. 

I will never forget what my grandmother said to me. She said, "don't ever let a man abuse you." I then asked my self how do I do that? 

A long conversation I have been having with myself, other women and little girls.
Sometimes we ladies give way to this evil act to keep happening to us . Now we have to help each other in how we can prevent and stop this evil thing from living amongst us. 

Many have died already.
